cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on visual ego-motion estimation for autonomous robots. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the paper proposes a fully trainable solution for visual ego-motion estimation. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the proposed architecture uses a Mixture Density Network (MDN) and Conditional Variational Autoencoder (C-VAE) for learning. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper proposes a self-supervised learning approach for visual ego-motion estimation. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also relevant as the paper discusses the use of standard navigation-based sensor fusion strategies for bootstrapped ego-motion learning in robots.
